704209f-a.text:
502 Flatbush Ave., west side, opposite Lefferts Ave., showing a two story frame house possibly belonging at one time to one Neefus. In the realty Atlas of Brooklyn (1929) there is a three story structure on the
site, of either stone or stucco.
About 1920.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
704209f-a.folder: Flatbush Avenue & Lefferts Avenue, Brooklyn, NY

704210f-b.text:
(1)
Flatbush Ave., west side, at Lefferts Ave. In the center background, 508-514 Flatbush Ave., which was formerly the Willink family's
home. In the foreground, at left, is Washington Ave.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
Same, showing the Willink home. Also seen is the Flatbush Ave.,
trolley line.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
